Description: Neck and shoulder sherd of Chian pottery closed vessel, possibly an oinochoe; white slip; exterior: slip mostly lost with traces of streaky black bands; ridge at junction of neck and shoulder; inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: Chian oinochoai are not common at Naukratis.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GD.0055) (phase 2)
